         <div type="transcription">
            <p>
<lb corresp="#a1"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><gap reason="plain" unit="part"/>ts<surplus>ä</surplus></w><w>w<gap reason="plain" unit="part"/>s</w><w>ś<gap reason="plain" unit="part"/></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a2"/><gap reason="lost"/><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><w>m</w><w>wālätkāñ</w><w>a</w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a3"/><gap reason="lost"/><gap reason="plain" quantity="2"/><w>yoktsi</w><w>yo</w><w>wā</w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a4"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><gap reason="plain" unit="part"/></w><w>ts<gap reason="plain" unit="part"/>ātär</w><pc>॥</pc><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b1"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>r<surplus>ä</surplus></w><pc>॥</pc><w>sa</w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b2"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>täm</supplied>näṣtär</w><w>k<gap reason="plain" unit="part"/></w><w>t<gap reason="plain" unit="part"/></w><w>l<gap reason="plain" unit="part"/></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b3"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>ka</supplied>pśañi</w><w>sne</w><w>prākron<supplied>e</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b4"/><gap reason="lost"/><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><w>ārlune</w><w>lā</w><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><gap reason="lost"/></p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... turtles ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... drink ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... is born ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... body without solidity ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... ceasing ...</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="remarks">According to three different labels on the frame, this fragment may belong together with <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a154"/>. The reason for this is evidently the word <hi>wālätkāñ</hi>, which occurs in line a2 of this fragment as well as in <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a154"/> a5. I have not yet found more precise matches proving that the two fragments belong to the same leaf.</note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment">: cf. <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a154"/> a5 <hi>tmäṣ tom wālätkāñ kaṣtyo miṣānt</hi> 'then these turtles were tortured by hunger'. The translation 'turtles' follows <bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>256</citedRange></bibl>.</note><note corresp="#a4" type="philcomment"><hi>ts·ātär</hi>: perhaps <hi>ts(k)ātär</hi> 'will be pulled out', cf. <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a154"/> a4 <hi>śākant</hi> 'were pulled out'.</note></p>
         </div>
